"   <div id=\"basicsTopicLeft\">",
"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Hydrocephalus (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/hydrocephalus-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111754998\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is hydrocephalus?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Hydrocephalus the medical term for when there is too much spinal fluid in the brain. Spinal fluid is fluid that surrounds and protects the brain and spinal cord. In some people, too much spinal fluid can put pressure on the brain. Hydrocephalus is sometimes called &ldquo;water on the brain.&rdquo;",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      This article focuses on hydrocephalus in babies and children. Babies who are born too early or born with a brain problem are more likely to get hydrocephalus. A head injury or other problem that affects the brain can also cause the problem in people at any age.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111755013\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of hydrocephalus?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;In babies, the main symptom is a head that:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Is bigger than normal",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Grows larger very fast",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Has an odd shape",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Has an outward bulge at the soft spot on the top of the head",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Has veins that bulge out",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      In older babies and children, symptoms can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        A head that is bigger than normal",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Headaches (often in the morning)",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Eyes that stay looking down and cannot look up",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling sick (nausea) and throwing up (vomiting)",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Not feeling hungry",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling sleepy",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111755028\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for hydrocephalus?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. In newborns, doctors use an ultrasound, a test that uses sound waves to take pictures of the brain. The doctor or nurse also measures the baby&rsquo;s head to see how fast it is growing. In older children, doctors use other imaging tests such as an MRI or CT scan to take a picture of the brain.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      The doctor might also do a &ldquo;lumbar puncture&rdquo; (sometimes called a &ldquo;spinal tap&rdquo;). During this procedure, he or she puts a thin needle into the child&rsquo;s lower back and removes a small amount of spinal fluid to check it for problems.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111755043\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is hydrocephalus treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Doctors treat hydrocephalus by putting a device called a &ldquo;shunt&rdquo; into the fluid-filled space inside the brain. The shunt is connected to a tube that is placed under the skin and that empties into the belly or heart. The shunt helps drain the extra spinal fluid from the brain (",
"      <a class=\"graphic graphic_figure graphicRef83273 \" href=\"mobipreview.htm?20/28/20932\">",
"       figure 1",
"      </a>",
"      ).",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Other possible treatments include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Surgery &ndash; In some cases, doctors do surgery to make a small opening in part of the brain to help drain excess spinal fluid. This surgery is called a &ldquo;third ventriculostomy.&rdquo; But it does not work for all types of hydrocephalus.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Medicines &ndash; Sometimes, doctors prescribe medicines that help the body make less spinal fluid.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111755058\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What will my child&rsquo;s life be like?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Many children treated for hydrocephalus grow up without any problems from it. But some have problems that need to be checked by a doctor right away. They include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        A problem with the shunt &ndash; Shunts sometimes get infected or stop working. If this happens, the child can get sick suddenly. The symptoms can include fever, headache, or vomiting.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Seizures &ndash; These are waves of abnormal electrical activity in the brain that can make a child pass out, or move or behave strangely.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Some children with hydrocephalus have brain damage that can cause a low &ldquo;IQ&rdquo; score. An IQ test can measure how well a person solves problems and understands things. Children with low IQ scores often need extra help in school.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H111755073\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can adults get hydrocephalus?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Adults can get hydrocephalus after a head injury or other problem with the brain. In some cases, adults have the same symptoms as children.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Some older adults get a type called &ldquo;normal pressure hydrocephalus.&rdquo; The symptoms include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Problems with thinking and memory",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Trouble walking",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Leaking urine or other bladder control problems",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      The tests and treatments for hydrocephalus in adults are the same as for children.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H61828516\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <a class=\"medical medical_basics\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?13/15/13555?source=see_link\">",
"       Patient information: Spina bifida (myelomeningocele) (The Basics)",
"      </a>",
"     </p>",
